Penetration testing (or ethical hacking) involves simulating cyberattacks to identify vulnerabilities in systems before malicious hackers exploit them. The process typically follows these stages:

Reconnaissance â€“ Gathering information about the target.

Scanning & Enumeration â€“ Identifying open ports, services, and vulnerabilities.

Exploitation â€“ Gaining unauthorized access using discovered vulnerabilities.

Post-Exploitation â€“ Maintaining access and escalating privileges.

Reporting & Remediation â€“ Documenting findings and suggesting fixes.

